okay, so I'm in my vertebrate zoology lab we have an assignment where we have to collect animals and key them out to species genus level and then show them to our TA. right? right. It's already s slightly stupid assignment, seeing as how if you collect what they tell you to (the minimum as they say) you get a C. Now, please correct me if I'm wrong, but if i bust my ass and find the 5 different fish (salt and freshwater) that they tell me too, toads, frogs, lizards, turtles and snakes (yes, multiples of each) and 3 different mammals (2 of which can't be rodents).....i'm gonna get a C? I call total bullshit on that. If i get all the crap they tell me to, i should get an A....isn't that how school works? To get an A you have to bring in extra stuff and rare animals. So now my grade all comes down on how many animals i can catch and how rare they are...nice. So that s the first thing this rants about, but not the main focus.

I think its extremely cruel to the animals when the school sends out untrained students (of which they have taught none how to safely trap an animal) and have them haul the animals back into class on Friday. More than half of the people go out hunting on the weekends, and while my TA i willing to meet people outside of class to mark off the specimen, almost everyone waits till Friday to show her. Which means most of these people have the animals they have caught sitting and starving in water bottles or bare portable terrariums. Last Friday some guys brought in a young Javelina in a large dog kennel. The poor things snout was bleeding freely from ramming into the cage and was foaming at the corners of its mouth from smacking its lips together in a vain attempt to warn the 20 people who were crowding around its cage 'AWWWWWWWW-ing' loudly. The guys that brought the javelina in got it checked off and left with it. I'm hoping they released it, but as wild pigs are seen as a pest, probably not. Today however, was almost as much as i could take. This guy caught a raccoon in a trap and brought it in. The poor thing was scared to death and so stressed out it was trembling. He left it in the bright florescent lighting near the door where everyone was tramping around and right next to the cart where all the jars of the reptiles we were keying out where everyone kept getting stuff off of and slamming down jars. There was a huge crowd of people with the faces mashed up next to the trap loudly exclaiming how sorry they felt for it while the poor raccoon huddle in the corner. When i expressed my concern about the raccoon to the guy who brought it in, he said, "he's having a great time, he got 2 tamales out of it, and look how much fun he's having!" It took every millimeter of self restraint in me not to slap him across the face. This one girl spent much of the class sitting next to it, telling it how sorry she was and how she wanted to let it go. She kept taking pictures of it (with her really loud camera). I may not be an animal expert, but i do have fucking common sense. Sitting there talking to the animal and pressing her face up to the side of the cage is not going to help it!!!! You want to help the animal, sit your ass down!!! The guy who brought it in had a towel that he eventually dropped on top pf the cage with no thought as the raccoon jumped). At the time I was getting a snake of the cart so i opened up the towel and spread it so it covered the top and the side of the cage that faced the door. So after i sit back down, the stupid girl kept going up to the trap and lifting up the towel and STILL talking to it. When the guy took it outside, after about 2 hours, he put it in the bed of his truck and came back inside!! Many people had already left the lab and the TA told him he could leave to release it. Its times like this that i wish i could murder. Those of you who know me know how i feel about animal cruelty, (and this i feel was def. animal cruelty). It really broke my heart. and started my day off bad.

Home from Thanksgiving. It was wonderful. Traveling home for Holidays makes me feel so grown up. And restored. There's nothing better for my spirit than spending time in the place i grew up, surrounded by family. Finding remnants of all my old hopes and dreams. It's very inspiring to me. While i was home i snooped (is it tech. snooping when its your room?) through all me old stuff from High School and earlier. It was just what i needed. I've felt so drained and defeated lately, but looking through all my old birthday cards, locker signs, notes, and just scraps of stuff i got this amazing feeling of love and happiness wash over me. It was amazing. And i thought...maybe i can do this :). There's almost a mantra of things i tell myself, through bad days, horrible dance rehearsals where i feel so frustrated that its all i can do not to cry, late nights studying, times when i get so mad i wanna scream, and moments where i know if i sit down i'll never get up. 1. You Are Not the Audience. This came from one of my romance novels of all places, and the moment i read it i could not get it out of my head. It helps remind me that I am the lead in my life and to do what makes me happy, not what others tell me will make me happy. 2.Defy Gravity. Oh Wicked. If i could play any song so loud that my eardrums almost burst it would be this one. I have this written in huge green letters on my mirror so that i see it every day. Reminds me to reach for the stars. 3. Now is Real. The other day in yoga class my teacher was basically saying this: The past no longer exists, the future may never exist. The only real thing in life is this moment. now. now. now. And as humans we never live in the now. We relive the past, plan the future, and never even notice now. I had never really thought about that before, i mean, really thought about it. After any horrible disaster or tragedy, it's easy to realize how fragile life is and how you have to live each moment as your last. Whats hard is actually doing it. And my teacher explained that it's hard because in this moment, now, your brain can only observe. it can't plan or review. You have no control.....and somehow, i like that thought. Now, that in no way excuses laziness or unpreparedness. Its just a nudge to stop everything for a moment, and let go of your control. Try it, its good for you :). 4. I Am Loved. Cause i am, by all sorts of people. It helps me when i feel worthless. 5. YOU Are the Only One Who Can Bring Happiness or Unhappiness to Your Life.Another Yoga lesson, one that i'm finding to be very true.

I'm so over my life. I mean, i'm 20 years old, thats 2 decades, and what have i done with it? nothing. I've never been outside the US, never even gone that many places IN the US.

I mean sure, i've gone to school, made it into college, and am working hard towards becoming a exotic animal vet, a career that i really don't have a chance in hell at making. But hey, i'm not giving up. I have wonderful friends that will always support me no matter what, and my family has always been extremely loving towards me. They've never put down any of my dreams or ambitions, never laughed at my feelings, and have given me nothing but support and help no matter what path i choose. I never fear that i will disappoint them(with the exception of getting my tattoo, and even that's not a big thing). I am strong in my faith, it may not be the most conventional faith, but i know God loves and protects me.

So why then do i feel so dissatisfied with everything? I know it sounds like i'm bitching about nothing. I have the type of life some people would love to have. I have a family who loves me, i may not have a lot of money, but i've never wanted for food or warmth or even clothes.

Maybe thats the trouble. I've never really had to work hard to get anything. Getting into Incarnate Word was easy. I didn't work that hard in high school, but still got into the college i wanted. I've never really been turned down for anything. And somewhere in the back of my mind thinks that i've got a sure shot to getting into Vet school, even though my grades are pretty crappy and only the top 132 students get into A&M's vet program. And you can bet that those top 132 students have nothing but As. So why would they chose me, a less than mediocre student with Bs and Cs? They won't, but my mind doesn't believe that anything will prevent that.

I'm not a spoiled brat. When it comes to material things i have very rarely gotten what i really wanted. Growing up in a slightly below middle class family there was never that much money to spend on frivolous things. It just seems when it comes to the important big stuff in life, i've always gotten my way.

This is why i've decided to go on a cross country road trip. I was reading this one woman's blog about how she went from San Fransisco to New York on her Vespa, and how it totally changed her life. Thats what i need, some amazing life changing experience. I need to go thousands of miles from anything i've known, lose myself, and then start to find who i really am. I know there are millions of things out there in this world bigger than me, i've seen amazing pictures on TV and the internet, but I need to see them myself. I need to realize what a small role i play in this world.

I need to change my life.

So, i'm planning on the summer after i graduate college. I figure thats just about the right timing. HAHA i just wish i was starting tomorrow.

So i went to my A&M Corpus Christi Orientation Thursday and Friday. It was sooooo amazing. I love it down there. I really think i'm gonna like it. So Thursday was the main sign in and everything, and then Friday was this big all day thing for New Students. It was really fun. I met some people who seemed really cool and we seem to get along really well. So when my mom and i got there on Thursday, the sign in didn't start until 4, and we got there a little after noon, so we grabbed some towels and headed down to the beach which was really cool. Except there were jellyfish everywhere! My mom and i could barely walk down the beach there were so many! So we were sitting there on the sand, gazing longingly into the ocean, really mad and disappointed that we weren't gonna be able to get into the water, when we decieded, consequences be damned! We're gonna o in the ocean. Which we did. And we didn't get stung. It was awsome. There was hardly any seaweed, and the waves we big and perfect. Wonderful time. So during orientation we sign up for our classes and all of us are assigned a academic advisor, mie was Johm Moury. So i sit down with him and he asks me, so what do you wanna be when you grow up? And i already had all the classes i wanted to take planned so we were done registering me in like, two mins and he goes, wow, i've never really had the time to advise at these things. So we sat there for another 10 mins talking about my future, which was really cool. It really calmed me down about things. And it turns out that i chose the hardest major in the world to take-biomedical science with a minor in theatre....hahah crazy i know. Buuuut i think i'm gonna have to drop that minor, cause uhm Biomedical science with a pre-vet career plan....not gonna be easy..AT ALL. But after being there i know i can do it. It's gonna be the hardest thing i've probably ever done, but i'll do it. And i got my housing. Since it was so late that i turned it in, all they had left were two bedroom apartments which is Fucking AWSOME! i'm gonna have an apartment! thats CRAZY!!! yep. too cool. WEDNESDAYS Same as Mondays THURSDAYS 11:00-12:15 --> Theatre 2:00- 4:00 --> 2 HOUR BIO LAB And now for the best day... FRIDAYS 9:00-9:50 --> Chemistry 11:00-11:50 --> Biology AND THATS IT!!! so i've been having nightmares almost nightly now, and it scares me so much because so many of them are about my mom dying.

After i had the first one last week, it woke me up at like, 6 in the morning when my mom was getting ready for work. And i ran to her and hugged her and told her i had a bad dream about her dying and she was like, "its okay, it was just a bad dream, go back to sleep" which of course i couldn't, and besides, i was gonna get up in like 30 mins anyway to watch Buffy and Angel and Charmed, which fits into this story actually. So my parents leave and i go in the living room and i'm watching Angel and i switch the channel over to Buffy.....and its the episode where her mother dies. And that like, REALLY freaked me out. And those of you who know me pretty well know how oppsesive and worried i get over stuff like that. So, i go through the day, not really thinking about it, and then that afternoon on Law and Order, someone's mother gets murdered. And that freaked me out even more. So my mom gets home and i didn't think about it very much after that and we went out to get dinner and when we got home i was telling my mom and dad about all the crazy stuff that freaked me out and my mom says, "i'm glad i didn't tell you this this morning Rachel, cause i knew tht you'd freak out and worry about it, but this morning when i was in the shower, i had a prememnition that i was going to die." and of coue, that just......scared the hell out of me. So i like, spent the whole night sitting by my mom watching her.

And that fer has not gone away. My mom (and what i'm trying to tll myself) thinks that she had that bad feeling cause thats when o was having my bad deam and i mean, that makes sense that she could tell when i was haveing a really bad nightmare.

And my dad tells me that haveing nightmares like that are very commen around the time of senior year and when you go away to college cause thats when you start to make your own decisions and you really start to fear losing it all.

and it seems that almost every year at Incarnate Word someone's mother dies and that really scares me and......i don't know.....life is just really scary.

On another note, my mom found like, 3 huge boxes filled with baby pictures of me and my brother and some of her when she was young and some of my dad's family and everything. and my grandfather (my dad's dad who died when he was 13) looks sooooooo much like Mel Gibson......make that a mean looking Mel Gibson. I think i must have been REALLY annoying when i was a little kid, i look like i was. However, there are a few where i look relaltively cute.

 its just crazy to think that i've gone from looking like that, to this

Today...was not a very good day. It was really hard watching Tiffany deal with all of this grief and i wish that i could know how it felt so that i could better help her with it.

When i was talking to my mom about it on Saturday she said that she was glad Tiffany wasn't dating him anymore, because there would have been a chance she would have been in the car.

And thats what i told Tiff today. We were standing outside the door at St. A's and she said that she loved him so much and she didn't understand why he let her go. And i started really crying and said that if he hadn't, that she might have been there, and that would have been something i could never had delt with. Everything happens in this lifetime for a reason.

To tell you all the truth, i was seriously contemplating the exsistance of God on Saturday night, and i wonder if its just my blind faith, buit i know deep in my soul that he is there, and that makes it easier to go through this, because i have someone to yell at and to ask "why" to, and even though he doesn't answer, i can still feel him there.

I didn't know Michael that well, i just knew him when Tiff was dating him and then during Pride and Prejudice. I think i even hated him for a while for wht he did to Tiff, and i'm very very angry at him for what he did to everyone else. but theres something about death that changes all that, you look back in yuour memory and just think about little times. God, he wqs just here a second ago, and now he's not.

I think thats the hardest thing for me to deal with, the fleetingness of life. I mean, sure, evberyone says to embrace life, to live it like its your last day. But if you every really think about it, you don't. I know i don't. I let so many things get in the way of doing what i really want to do or saying what i really want to say. Because if you think about, so many times we part with those we love with angry words, or not saying the words that we truley wanted to say at some point.

So i know this all sounds really cliche, but guys, make sure that those you love know youi love them. Hug your parents and tell them how much they mean to you. Don't let anything get in the way of your friendships, especially petty things that don't matter.

I just want all of ya'll to know that i truley love and care very deeply for all of ya'll.
